        <abstract>
            <p>Answers JS’s criticism of natural selection, which he doubts JS understands. CD does not believe in an "innate selective principle".</p>
            <p>To understand "utility" JS should read CD on correlation.</p>
            <p>Origin of maize: no longer thinks husked form was wild because of Asa Gray’s evidence on its variability.</p>
            <p>Has information from Thomas Rivers on weeping habit in trees.</p>
            <p>JS’s experiments on coloured primroses.</p> 
<p>Encloses bibliographical note on <hi rend="italic">Passiflora</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
